  <div class="rlo-content-body col-xs-12 rlo-content-bottom">

    <div class="rlo-content-memo"> A change of direction </div>
      
  The scattered X-ray photon differs in two respects from the incident photon.
  The direction of travel is altered, and the photon energy is lower than the incident photon energy.
  This can be though of a 'blue' photon scattering to a 'red' one.

